rop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/top-view-of-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/top-view-of-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"4096\" height=\"2304\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Top view of the monitor light bar\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/top-view-of-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/top-view-of-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWorking in the dark means that your eyes are constantly strained due to the contrast between the dark surroundings and the bright screen. No matter how much you reduce your screen\u0026#39;s brightness, it\u0026#39;s always going to be brighter than your surroundings. This can lead to sore or watery eyes, both of which are harmful and can have long-term implications.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eWhat a light bar does is reduce this contrast by lighting up the surroundings ever so slightly. It\u0026#39;s not harsh enough to bother you, while also being sufficiently bright to reduce the fatigue caused to your eyes. After using a light bar for a week, I could sense that my eyes felt less tired than they did without it.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"improves-focus-and-productivity\"\u003e\n                        Improves focus and productivity\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"only-lights-up-the-required-portions\"\u003e\n            Only lights up the required portions\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eIt\u0026#39;s rather simple to get distracted when working late at night, since you\u0026#39;re probably tired and sleepy at the end of the day. Owing to this, I used to lose focus and while away time scrolling on my smartphone, or end up shutting down my PC and going to bed. Surprisingly, the light bar even helped me overcome my procrastination by allowing me to focus on my work.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThis is because of the position in which the light bar is mounted. It rests on top of the monitor and emits light downwards, highlighting the screen and everything on the desk, including the keyboard and the mouse. This focused light source ensures your attention is on the screen, as opposed to a lamp or lightbulb. Moreover, it also helps with typing if you\u0026#39;re not a touch typist or your keyboard doesn\u0026#39;t have backlit keys. You can easily view all the keys on the keyboard without guessing their positions in the dark.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"no-more-glare-or-reflections\"\u003e\n                        No more glare or reflections\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"distraction-free-visuals\"\u003e\n            Distraction-free visuals\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/using-the-monitor-with-a-light-bar.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/using-the-monitor-with-a-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/using-the-monitor-with-a-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/using-the-monitor-with-a-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/using-the-monitor-with-a-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/using-the-monitor-with-a-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/using-the-monitor-with-a-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/using-the-monitor-with-a-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/using-the-monitor-with-a-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"4096\" height=\"2304\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Using the monitor with a light bar\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/using-the-monitor-with-a-light-bar.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/using-the-monitor-with-a-light-bar.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMy biggest annoyance with bright light sources is that they create reflections on the monitor screen, especially if you have a glossy display without an anti-glare coating. Due to the diffused nature of a monitor light bar and the angle at which it projects light, you won\u0026#39;t have any reflections or glare issues, even when used with super-reflective screens.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eOne thing to note, though, is that you need a light bar that\u0026#39;s large enough to cover the entire width of the monitor. While the light bar itself may not be as big, you\u0026#39;ll have to ensure that the coverage of the light emitted from it spans the entire width of your monitor. I have a 34-inch ultra-wide monitor, and in hindsight, I should have opted for a larger size since the light bar I got is for standard 16:9 displays. This is something to keep in mind since you want to make sure all parts of your monitor are evenly lit up. It\u0026#39;s also slightly harder to mount on a curved monitor.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"makes-your-setup-more-attractive\"\u003e\n                        Makes your setup more attractive\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"it-even-has-rgb\"\u003e\n            It even has RGB!\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/rgb-lighting-on-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/rgb-lighting-on-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/rgb-lighting-on-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/rgb-lighting-on-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/rgb-lighting-on-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/rgb-lighting-on-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/rgb-lighting-on-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/rgb-lighting-on-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/rgb-lighting-on-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"4096\" height=\"2304\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"RGB lighting on the monitor light bar\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/rgb-lighting-on-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/04/rgb-lighting-on-the-monitor-light-bar.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI got a monitor light bar from Quntis, and the variant I have has three different color temperatures to choose from. I prefer the warm white option since it causes less strain to the eyes. It\u0026#39;s advisable to stay away from blue light at night, so the warm, yellowish tint is the perfect hue. Additionally, there\u0026#39;s also an RGB light strip at the top of the bar that shines light onto the wall behind my monitor to create an extra visual effect. If you\u0026#39;re a gamer or have RGB lighting as a part of your PC setup, you\u0026#39;re surely going to appreciate this. If you find it too distracting, though, you can always turn it off.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"an-absolute-must-if-you-work-in-the-dark\"\u003e\n                        An absolute must if you work in the dark\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you\u0026#39;re like me and you spend a substantial amount of time in front of a screen in low-light situations, I would highly recommend getting a light bar for your monitor. Not just for work, but gamers who spend hours in front of a screen in the dark will also appreciate the changes a light bar brings to the table -- quite literally. While there are \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/benq-screen-bar-pro-review/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003epremium options available from BenQ\u003c/a\u003e, any standard light bar that\u0026#39;s big enough to cover a good portion of your monitor will do the job.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
